cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computation over a communication network with capacity constraints. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with distributed data and computation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper formulates linear programs to determine network flows that maximize the computation rate. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with designing computing and communicating schemes to obtain the function at the maximum rate. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper develops a fast combinatorial primal-dual algorithm to obtain approximate solutions to the linear programs.
